# 📝 Key Takeaways

- SSH provides secure remote administration.
- OpenSSH is the default SSH implementation on Ubuntu.
- SSH Client starts the connection.
- SSH Server accepts the connection.
- NAT allows many private devices to share one public IP.
- PAT uses port numbers to distinguish multiple network connections.

